cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.SD, cs.HC

The paper analyzes the productivity patterns of faculty in computer science departments, making it likely to fall under the categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.SD (Software Engineering), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). The study uses a large bibliographic dataset and comprehensive information on career transitions, which suggests a focus on social and information networks, digital libraries, and human-computer interaction. Additionally, the study explores correlations between productivity trajectories and researcher covariates, which could fall under the category of computers and society. Finally, the study focuses on productivity patterns in computer science departments, which could fall under the category of software engineering.
